ious expectations of them. With chapters on prominent soldiers past and present, Ebel recovers and re-narrates the stories of the common American men and women that live and die at both the center and edges of public consciousness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 0aSoldierszUnited StatesxPublic opinion. 0aWarxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300216356423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300216356.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO